Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteBufferTree(25.10)                                deleteBufferTree(25.10)

Name
       deleteBufferTree  - Removes all buffers (except clock path buffers) and
       inverter pairs, of all footprint types, on all nets in the design

Syntax
       deleteBufferTree

       [-help]

       [-excNetFile <excFileName>]

       [-footprint <footPrintName>]

       [-preserveRoute]

       [-selNetFile <selF><ileName |>-net<list_of_nets>]

       [-verbose]

       Removes all buffers (except clock path buffers) and inverter pairs,  of
       all footprint types, on all nets in the design. With specific settings,
       this  command  can  remove  buffers and inverter pairs of the specified
       footprint type, or on specified nets only.

       Note:

              * place_opt_design will automatically call  deleteBufferTree  in
                the beginning, before global placement.

              * If  you  want  to have a clean design with reduced density, or
                just clear all buffers and inverter pairs of a certain list of
                nets, it is recommended to call this command. This  may  allow
                you to do ECO on those nets.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each deleteBufferTree parameter.  For  a  detailed
              description  of  the  command and all of its parameters, use the
              man command:  man deleteBufferTree

       -excNetFile <excFileName>
              Specifies the input file that contains the names of nets to  ex-
              clude  from buffer removal. If a net appears in the files speci-
              fied by both -excNetFile and -selNetFile, it is excluded.

       -footprint <footprintName>
              Specifies the footprint of buffers to  remove.  If  you  do  not
              specify  this parameter, the Innovus software removes buffer in-
              stances with one input and one output terminal, and whose timing
              arc is not SPECIAL.

       -net <list_of_nets>
              Specifies the hierarchical nets to  include  during  buffer  re-
              moval.

              Note:  The  -net  and -selNetFile parameters are mutually exclu-
              sive.

       -preserveRoute
              Specifies that nets not impacted by the buffer/inverter deletion
              process must have their routing unchanged. By default, the  tool
              removes all the routes after running this command.

       -selNetFile <selF><ileName>
              Specifies  the file that contains the names of hierarchical nets
              to include during buffer  removal.  The  software  excludes  all
              other nets. If a net appears in the files specified by both -ex-
              cNetFile and -selNetFile, it is excluded.

              Note:  The  -net  and -selNetFile parameters are mutually exclu-
              sive.

       -verbose
              When specified, displays additional debug messages in log  file.
              For  example,  the failure reason for deletion of buffer and in-
              verter pairs.

Examples
              * The following command removes all buffers and inverter  pairs,
                of all footprint types:

                deleteBufferTree

                *** Start deleteBufferTree ***

                Info: Detect buffers to remove automatically.

                Analyzing netlist ...

                Updating netlist

                *summary: 79 instances (buffers/inverters) removed

                *** Finish deleteBufferTree (0:00:09.6) ***

              * The  following  command  removes all buffers of footprint type
                B_1P:

                deleteBufferTree -footprint B_1P

